result.execSummary:
The defendant Lanile Kimbrough was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.
  • Possess w/Intent to Deliver Controlled Substance-(MDMA) (>10-50g), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(hm)3.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison.
Consecutive to: consecutive to any other sentence and concurrent with Count 2 in 15CF1959, with credit for 2 days (05-13-2015 and 05-14-2015) time served.

miscConds.notes: AS TO EACH COUNT:  Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.

Regularly participate in an HSED or GED program until completed. 
Maintain fulltime employment/school or a combination of both.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
Defendant may not live where a firearm is kept. 
Defendant may not be in any automobile where a firearm is present.

No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
Defendant is not to possess cash currency in an amount greater than $200.00 at one time.
No possession of more than one cell phone at any one time.
Defendant my not have more than one phone number registered to you name at one time. 
Defendant to not associate with any known gang member, associate or affiliate. 
Geographic are restriction within area bordered on:
North by West Townsend Street, Milwaukee WI  
South by West Locust Street, Milwaukee WI 
East by North 20th Street, Milwaukee WI 
West by North 30th Street, Milwaukee WI

Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days of receiving prescription from medical professional.
Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by Department of Corrections Agent, and notify the Department of Corrections agent of the pharmacy used. 
Defendant to participate in a Cognitive Behavior program.
Curfew for the first 18 months of probation from 7:00 pm to 6:00 am, unless verified work or school hours, 
Fine is set at ZERO.
Drivers License set at ZERO. 
Provide DNA sample, if not already done.

Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.  
Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing.
**3/1/2016  Defendant is no longer eligible for expungement.

AS TO COUNT 1 -
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence and concurrent with Count 2 in 15CF1959, with credit for 2 days (05-13-2015 and 05-14-2015) time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS

AS TO COUNT 2 -
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence and concurrent with Count 1 in 15CF1959, with credit for 2 days (05-13-2015 and 05-14-2015) time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS.
